---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title="Paradigms" description="Research paradigms — ontology, epistemology, methodology, and positivist, interpretivist, pragmatist views">
  <p class="back-link"><a href={`${base}research-questions/`}>← Research</a></p>
  <h1>Paradigms</h1>

  <section class="paradigms-section" aria-label="Understanding research paradigms">
    <h2 class="paradigms-heading">Understanding research paradigms*</h2>
    <p class="paradigms-prose">
      To better understand research methodology, <strong>researchers need an understanding of research paradigms</strong>.
      Paradigms can be described as <strong>different ways of viewing the world</strong> and often form the foundation from
      which research is undertaken. They consist of a set of <strong>assumptions about what is reality, how knowledge is
      created and what is valuable to learn</strong>. It is important that researchers are <strong>clear about their own
      beliefs and assumptions</strong> in this regard. In understanding paradigms and their impact upon the research
      process, <strong>researchers will be better positioned to understand the nature of research questions, why particular
      methodologies are used to answer those questions</strong> and how data collected is analysed and interpreted (Weaver and
      Olson, 2006). Consequently, this will <strong>assist researchers in developing a clearer understanding of how to
      critique research</strong>, how research results can be translated to their clinical practice and, ultimately, how to
      undertake research themselves (Scotland, 2012).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="paradigms-section" aria-label="Research paradigms">
    <h2 class="paradigms-heading">Research paradigms</h2>
    <div class="paradigms-diagram">
      <div class="paradigms-pillars" aria-label="Ontology, epistemology, and methodology">
        <div class="paradigms-pillar paradigms-pillar--methodology">
          <span class="paradigms-pillar-label">Methodology</span>
          <span class="paradigms-pillar-question">How can one investigate reality and/or knowledge?</span>
        </div>
        <div class="paradigms-pillar paradigms-pillar--ontology">
          <span class="paradigms-pillar-label">Ontology</span>
          <span class="paradigms-pillar-question">What is reality?</span>
        </div>
        <div class="paradigms-pillar paradigms-pillar--epistemology">
          <span class="paradigms-pillar-label">Epistemology</span>
          <span class="paradigms-pillar-question">What is knowledge?</span>
        </div>
        <span class="paradigms-center" aria-hidden="true">?</span>
      </div>
      <div class="paradigms-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</div>
      <ul class="paradigms-list">
        <li class="paradigms-item paradigms-item--positivist">
          <span class="paradigms-item-label">Positivist</span>
        </li>
        <li class="paradigms-item paradigms-item--interpretivist">
          <span class="paradigms-item-label">Interpretivist</span>
        </li>
        <li class="paradigms-item paradigms-item--pragmatist">
          <span class="paradigms-item-label">Pragmatist</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="paradigms-section paradigms-quote-section" aria-label="The rhetoric of positivism versus interpretivism">
    <h2 class="paradigms-heading">The Rhetoric of Positivism versus Interpretivism*</h2>
    <blockquote class="paradigms-quote">
      <p>
        &ldquo;For my part, however, I no longer want to be labeled <strong>as a positivist researcher or an interpretive
        researcher.</strong> It is time for us to move beyond labels and to see the underlying unity in what we are trying
        to achieve via our research methods. <strong>The commonalities in my view are compelling and paramount.</strong> The
        differences &hellip; should not divide us. The challenge for us is to rethink and develop a <strong>new rhetoric</strong>{' '}
        so we come to a <strong>deeper understanding of the meta theoretical assumptions that underlie our research.</strong>&rdquo;
      </p>
      <footer class="paradigms-quote-attribution">Ron Weber</footer>
    </blockquote>
    <p class="paradigms-footnote">*Adapted from Weber (2004).</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .back-link {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .back-link a {
    color: var(--color-maroon);
  }

  .paradigms-section {
    max-width: 44rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 1.75rem;
    background: #fff;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--color-maroon);
  }

  .paradigms-heading {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-maroon);
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
  }

  .paradigms-prose {
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    font-size: 0.98rem;
  }

  .paradigms-diagram {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }

  .paradigms-pillars {
    position: relative;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    grid-template-rows: auto auto;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 16rem;
    max-width: 22rem;
  }

  .paradigms-pillar {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.35;
  }

  .paradigms-pillar--methodology {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    justify-self: center;
    width: 9.5rem;
    background: rgba(100, 160, 220, 0.2);
    border: 2px solid rgba(80, 140, 200, 0.45);
  }

  .paradigms-pillar--ontology {
    background: rgba(230, 160, 90, 0.2);
    border: 2px solid rgba(210, 130, 60, 0.45);
  }

  .paradigms-pillar--epistemology {
    background: rgba(170, 130, 200, 0.2);
    border: 2px solid rgba(140, 100, 180, 0.45);
  }

  .paradigms-pillar-label {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .paradigms-pillar-question {
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
  }

  .paradigms-center {
    position: absolute;
    left: 50%;
    top: 58%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .paradigms-arrow {
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #e07830;
    line-height: 1;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .paradigms-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 10rem;
  }

  .paradigms-item {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .paradigms-item-label {
    display: block;
    padding: 0.55rem 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .paradigms-item--positivist .paradigms-item-label {
    background: rgba(80, 140, 200, 0.25);
    color: #2a5a8a;
  }

  .paradigms-item--interpretivist .paradigms-item-label {
    background: rgba(90, 170, 100, 0.25);
    color: #2a6a35;
  }

  .paradigms-item--pragmatist .paradigms-item-label {
    background: rgba(230, 140, 60, 0.25);
    color: #8a4a10;
  }

  .paradigms-item::after {
    content: '';
    display: block;
    height: 2.5rem;
    background: #fff;
  }

  .paradigms-quote {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    border: none;
  }

  .paradigms-quote p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    line-height: 1.65;
    font-size: 0.98rem;
    color: var(--color-ink);
  }

  .paradigms-quote-attribution {
    text-align: right;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }

  .paradigms-footnote {
    margin: 1rem 0 0 0;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-muted);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .paradigms-diagram {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: stretch;
    }

    .paradigms-arrow {
      text-align: center;
      transform: rotate(90deg);
    }

    .paradigms-pillars {
      max-width: none;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
  }
</style>
